<abstract>
<p>The distinction between costs and prices aggregates into the conflict between wages and profits in a macro-accounting framework. We exploit the Godley and Lavoie (2007) framework to derive a dynamical system in the variables. Deflation in at least one price is both necessary and sufficient for stability of the system.</p>
</abstract>
